Developing this software into something useful often requires adding to it or integrating it with other software. If you would like to contribute back to this software, the licensor will accept contributions under a different license.

### Copyright

The licensor has waived all copyright and related or neighboring rights to this software to the maximum extent possible under law.

### Notices

You must ensure that anyone who gets a copy of any part of this software from you also gets a copy of this license.

### Excuse

If anyone notifies you in writing that you have not complied with Notices, you can keep your license by taking all practical steps to comply within 30 days after the notice. If you do not do so, your license ends immediately.

### Patent

The licensor grants you a royalty-free, non-exclusive license, under any patent claims they can license, or become able to license, to do everything you would do without this license that this license otherwise requires.

### Reliability

The licensor will not revoke this license.

### No Liability

